# The `SCEVUnknown` Class Reference

<DoxygenPage pluginConfig={pluginConfig}>

## Description {#details}

This means that we are dealing with an entirely unknown <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/scev">SCEV</a> value, and only represent it as its LLVM <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/value">Value</a>.

This is the &quot;bottom&quot; value for the analysis.

## Private Member Functions

### allUsesReplacedWith() {#aba6a7779a2b926986f2e917c11d30695}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>void SCEVUnknown::allUsesReplacedWith (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/value">Value</a> &#42;)</>}
  labels = {["virtual"]}>
Callback for <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/value">Value</a> RAUW.

Called when this-&gt;<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/valuehandlebase/#a7d6d2457c839e340266704440f3bb243">getValPtr()</a>-&gt;replaceAllUsesWith(new&#95;value) is called, <em>before</em> any of the uses have actually been replaced. If <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/weaktrackingvh">WeakTrackingVH</a> were implemented as a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/callbackvh">CallbackVH</a>, it would use this method to call setValPtr(new&#95;value). <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/assertingvh">AssertingVH</a> would do nothing in this method.

Declaration at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/analysis/scalarevolutionexpressions-h/#l00595">595</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/analysis/scalarevolutionexpressions-h">ScalarEvolutionExpressions.h</a>, definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/analysis/scalarevolution-cpp/#l00561">561</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/analysis/scalarevolution-cpp">ScalarEvolution.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

### deleted() {#a031fe5736de3679ef23d8e360a9a20fb}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="void SCEVUnknown::deleted ()"
  labels = {["virtual"]}>
Callback for <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/value">Value</a> destruction.

Called when this-&gt;<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/valuehandlebase/#a7d6d2457c839e340266704440f3bb243">getValPtr()</a> is destroyed, inside ~Value(), so you may call any non-virtual <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/value">Value</a> method on <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/valuehandlebase/#a7d6d2457c839e340266704440f3bb243">getValPtr()</a>, but no subclass methods. If <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/weaktrackingvh">WeakTrackingVH</a> were implemented as a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/callbackvh">CallbackVH</a>, it would use this method to call setValPtr(NULL). <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/assertingvh">AssertingVH</a> would use this method to cause an assertion failure.

All implementations must remove the reference from this object to the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/value">Value</a> that&#39;s being destroyed.

Declaration at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/analysis/scalarevolutionexpressions-h/#l00594">594</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/analysis/scalarevolutionexpressions-h">ScalarEvolutionExpressions.h</a>, definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/analysis/scalarevolution-cpp/#l00550">550</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/analysis/scalarevolution-cpp">ScalarEvolution.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>
